title: For Sale:  AR-15 "Mock Dissipator" 5.56/.223 Rifle
postcontent: Put about 100 rounds through it, it's been flawless.  I wanted to build a high quality "stealth gray" mock Dissipator, hate to see her go on the selling block.  Effort was put into getting quality PSA, Magpul, CMMG and Aero Precision bolt parts.  Selling because of financial reasons.In case you're not sure what "Dissipator" is, it's a carbine length (16" barrel) AR15 with a rifle length gas sytem and front sight, the idea being you have a long sight radius.  They also look really cool. :)  Real Dissipators had problems, though, because the gas system wasn't made for carbine length barrels.  A "mock" Dissipator like this one means the front sight block is purely for looks and for using your iron sights.  It actually has a reliable low profile mid-length gas block underneath the handguard.  So you get all the looks and benefits of a Dissipator but none of the reliability problems!Onto the nuts and bolts, here are the parts used in this build:PSA "mock Dissipator" barreled upper receiver.Anderson lower receiver with CMMG parts kit.  ALG QMS trigger, which if you're not familiar with is made by Geissele and gives a super crisp ~5.5lb break so it's still mil-spec for any range or competition rules about such things.Aero Precision Black Nitride Complete Bolt Carrier GroupMagpul CTR Stock, "Stealth Gray" Magpul MOE+ Grip,  "Stealth Gray"Magpul Rifle Length Handguards (heat shielded), "Stealth Gray."Magpul Gen2 MBUS Rear Sight, Black
